==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scythian
<hw>Scyth"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Scythia (a name given to the northern part of Asia, and Europe adjoining
to Asia), or its language or inhabitants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scythian lamb</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Barometz</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scythian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scythian
<hw>Scyth"i*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or
inhabitant of Scythia; specifically <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>, one of a
Slavonic race which in early times occupied Eastern Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The language of the Scythians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scytodermata</ent>⟦br⟧
